                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.765,
                                "byte_start": 86044,
                                "byte_stop": 133169,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 97-1868, UNUM Life Insurance Company of America versus Ward will be announced by Justice Ginsburg."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.765,
                        "stop": 270.72,
                        "byte_start": 133169,
                        "byte_stop": 1168872,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.765,
                                "stop": 20.071,
                                "byte_start": 133169,
                                "byte_stop": 166397,
                                "text": "This case concerns the Employee Retirement Income Security Act ERISA is its acronym."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.071,
                                "stop": 27.806,
                                "byte_start": 166397,
                                "byte_stop": 197326,
                                "text": "It is complex legislation and it is a constant supplier of questions in need of adjudication."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.806,
                                "stop": 35.912,
                                "byte_start": 197326,
                                "byte_stop": 229717,
                                "text": "Two of ERISA\u0027s most litigated clauses, the Preemptions Clause and the Saving Clause are again at issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.912,
                                "stop": 47.109,
                                "byte_start": 229717,
                                "byte_stop": 274544,
                                "text": "The Preemption Clause broadly states that ERISA provisions shall supersede state laws that relate to any employee benefit plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.109,
                                "stop": 58.447,
                                "byte_start": 274544,
                                "byte_stop": 319892,
                                "text": "The Saving Clause prays with similar breadth exempts from preemption \u0022any law of any State which regulates insurance\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.447,
                                "stop": 71.884,
                                "byte_start": 319892,
                                "byte_stop": 373600,
                                "text": "The key words \u0022regulate insurance\u0022 in the Saving Clause and relate to in the Preemption Clause require interpretation for their meaning is not plain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.884,
                                "stop": 76.635,
                                "byte_start": 373600,
                                "byte_stop": 392617,
                                "text": "To apply ERISA sensibly we must measure its key words in context."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.635,
                                "stop": 90.384,
                                "byte_start": 392617,
                                "byte_stop": 447683,
                                "text": "The context here is a suit to recover disability benefits under an ERISA-governed policy issued by the defendant-petitioner UNUM Life Insurance Company."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.384,
                                "stop": 103.212,
                                "byte_start": 447683,
                                "byte_stop": 498988,
                                "text": "Plaintiff-respondent, John Ward submitted his proof of disability claim to UNUM outside the time limit set in the policy, and UNUM therefore denied Ward\u0027s application for benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.212,
                                "stop": 116.931,
                                "byte_start": 498988,
                                "byte_stop": 553845,
                                "text": "Ruling in Ward\u0027s favor and reversing the District Court\u0027s judgment for UNUM, the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit relied on decisional law in California, the State in which Ward worked."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.931,
                                "stop": 121.543,
                                "byte_start": 553845,
                                "byte_stop": 572235,
                                "text": "We affirm the Court of Appeals\u0027 judgment in Prime Part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.543,
                                "stop": 124.643,
                                "byte_start": 572235,
                                "byte_stop": 584669,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit\u0027s judgment rested on two grounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.643,
                                "stop": 142.669,
                                "byte_start": 584669,
                                "byte_stop": 656767,
                                "text": "That court relied first on California\u0027s \u0022notice-prejudice\u0022 rule, under which an insurer cannot avoid liability although the proof of claim is untimely, unless the insurer shows it was prejudiced by the delay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.669,
                                "stop": 151.794,
                                "byte_start": 656767,
                                "byte_stop": 693234,
                                "text": "The \u0022notice-prejudice\u0022 rule is saved from ERISA preemption, the Court of Appeals held, because it is law which regulates insurance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.794,
                                "stop": 153.099,
                                "byte_start": 693234,
                                "byte_stop": 698459,
                                "text": "We agree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.099,
                                "stop": 160.294,
                                "byte_start": 698459,
                                "byte_stop": 727298,
                                "text": "By its very terms, the \u0022notice-prejudice\u0022 rule is specifically directed at the insurance industr."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.294,
                                "stop": 185.31,
                                "byte_start": 727298,
                                "byte_stop": 827295,
                                "text": "Our opinion explains in detail why we are satisfied that the \u0022notice-prejudice\u0022 rule is not simply an industry-specific application of the general principle that law abhors a forfeiture rather it is a notably stringent adaptation of that principle of rule made mandatory only for insurance contracts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.31,
                                "stop": 202.584,
                                "byte_start": 827295,
                                "byte_stop": 896467,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals stated a second contingent ground for reversing the District Court\u0027s judgment for UNUM, one that would come into play only if on remand the insurer proved prejudice due to the delayed notice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.584,
                                "stop": 212.959,
                                "byte_start": 896467,
                                "byte_stop": 937949,
                                "text": "Under California decisions, the Ninth Circuit said, an employer could be deemed an agent of the insurer in administering group insurance policies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.959,
                                "stop": 219.624,
                                "byte_start": 937949,
                                "byte_stop": 964594,
                                "text": "Ward\u0027s employer knew of his disability within the time the policy allowed for proof of claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.624,
                                "stop": 230.614,
                                "byte_start": 964594,
                                "byte_stop": 1008584,
                                "text": "The generally applicable agency law of California the Ninth Circuit held, does not relate to employee benefit plans, and therefore is not preempted by ERISA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.614,
                                "stop": 247.629,
                                "byte_start": 1008584,
                                "byte_stop": 1076607,
                                "text": "We disagree with this contingent ruling deeming the employer or the agent of the insurer would have a marked effect on plan administration, forcing the employer to assume a role with attendant legal duties and consequences that the employer had not bargained for."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.629,
                                "stop": 259.098,
                                "byte_start": 1076607,
                                "byte_stop": 1122478,
                                "text": "We are therefore satisfied that the California agency law involved, does relate to ERISA plans and accordingly does not escape preemption."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.098,
                                "stop": 267.332,
                                "byte_start": 1122478,
                                "byte_stop": 1155393,
                                "text": "In sum, we affirm on the main ground the \u0022notice-prejudice\u0022 rule and reverse on the contingent employer as agent holding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 267.332,
                                "stop": 270.72,
                                "byte_start": 1155393,
                                "byte_stop": 1168872,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
